Workplace Wellness & Stress Survey

1. On average, how would you rate your stress levels during a typical workday?

A) Low – I feel calm and in control. 
B) Moderate – I feel pressure but can manage. (3/10)
C) High – I frequently feel overwhelmed. (4/10)
D) Extreme – I am on the verge of burnout. (3/10)

2. Which part of the office environment most negatively impacts your focus?

A) High noise levels (talking, phones, typing). (4/10)
B) Harsh or flickering overhead lighting. (3/10)
C) Lack of privacy or personal space. (3/10)
D) Uncomfortable temperature or poor air quality.

3. What is your "peak stress" time during the day?

A) Early morning (the "to-do list" panic). (2/10)
B) Mid-day (lunch rush/meeting marathons). (4/10)
C) Late afternoon (deadline pressure/fatigue). (4/10)
D) It is constant throughout the day.

4. When you feel a "stress spike," what is your immediate emotional reaction?

A) Irritability or frustration. (4/10)
B) Anxiety or a feeling of "doom." (3/10)
C) Mental fog or inability to make decisions. (3/10)
D) Apathy or a desire to leave the office immediately.

5. How much time can you realistically spare for a "stress break" without it disrupting your workflow?

A) Less than 5 minutes (Micro-break). (4/10)
B) 5–15 minutes (Standard session). (5/10)
C) 15–30 minutes (Deep relaxation). (1/10)
D) I don’t feel I can take breaks at all.

6. If you were in a private Pod, which lighting setting would help you "reset" fastest?

A) Blue/Cyan (to cool down and reduce anger). (2/10)
B) Warm Amber (to feel safe and comforted). (4/10)
C) Soft Green (to feel connected to nature). (2/10)
D) Total Darkness (to eliminate sensory overload). (2/10)

7. Which soundscape helps you enter a state of "Flow" or calm?

A) Nature sounds (Rain, Forest, Ocean). (3/10)
B) Ambient "Lo-fi" or Binaural beats. (3/10)
C) Guided vocal meditation. (2/10)
D) Pure White Noise / Silence. (2/10)

8. What prevents you from using existing wellness programs (like office yoga or workshops)?

A) Too time-consuming. (3/10)
B) Too public; I don't want to do it in front of peers. (4/10)
C) Not personalized to my specific needs. (2/10)
D) I simply forget they exist when I'm stressed. (1/10)

9. How do you feel about an AI tracking your stress via a wearable (e.g., heart rate)?

A) Very comfortable; I want the automation. (4/10)
B) Comfortable, as long as the data is private. (4/10)
C) Skeptical; I'd prefer to input my mood manually. (2/10)
D) Uncomfortable; I don't want my stress tracked.

10. What is your primary goal when using a Stress Relief Pod?

A) To stop a headache or physical tension. (2/10)
B) To calm my mind before a big event. (4/10)
C) To get a "boost" of energy to finish the day. (1/10)
D) To have 10 minutes of total isolation. (2/10)
